# Tooling notes (Linux / PC — this is the box this repo runs on)

- Use the venv's Python directly (no activation needed):
  - `./venv/bin/python -m pip install <pkg>`
  - `./venv/bin/python start.py`   # server on http://localhost:8002
  - `./venv/bin/python stop.py`
  - `./venv/bin/ruff check .`       # Python lint
- System deps **ffmpeg + VLC** are installed via apt on this box. `start.py` only
  auto-installs them on Windows; on Linux install them yourself.
- HTML lint: from `static/js`, run `npm install` (installs htmlhint), then `npm run lint:html`.
- JS lint: from `static/js`, `npm run lint`.
- Run/config/store details are in `AGENTS.md`; full setup + verification in
  `docs/local-setup-linux.md`.
